			<font face=helvetica size=-1>
<font face=helvetica size=3><b>Tuesday November 9, 1999</b></font>
			<hr align=LEFT size=1 width=500 color=#000080>
<!---------------news---------------->
<Br>
<font face=helvetica size=2 color=#000080><b>Q3A at Stomped</b> - 16:57:03</font>
<br><br><blockquote>
<a href=http://q3a.stomped.com/>Stomped Quake3Arena site</a> has opened up for business. It is very indepth and even tells you how to sit right so your back wont hurt playing too much. Now thats indepth. Heres the p00p...
<br><br><b>
Stomped.com's official Quake 3 site is now open for public
consumption.
<br><br>
It has been described as the most comprehensive Quake 3 site on the
internet -- and why not?  after all it took 9 months of construction!
<br><br>
It has a lot of information on the innerworkings of Quake 3 with a lot of
the information from id .plan files and emails directly to id employees
(Carmack, Steed, and Jacquays to name a few).  It has mailing lists.  A
discussion forum, level design tips, and a tonne of skinning and texture
tutorials.
<br><br></b>
The sites webmaster really knows his stuff because the editing section links back to rust as well as our Q3A site <a href=http://mapzone.gamedesign.net/>MapZone</a>. 

<b><p align=right>Update by <a href="mailto:raygunn@gamedesign.net">raYGunn</a></p></b>
</blockquote>
<h3>Go <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net">back</a> to the main news page...</h3>
			</font>
